   =20
      Are NFTs securities?
   =20
 =20

I   like to   explain crypto initial coin offerings by saying that =E2=80=
=9Cthey=E2=80=99re like if the Wright Brothers sold air miles to finance in=
venting the airplane,=E2=80=9D so here=E2=80=99s another old-timey analogy =
for non-fungible token offerings. Imagine that one day in the boom times of=
 the 1920s a young animator named Walter Disney shows up at the stock marke=
t one day looking to raise money for his new company. =E2=80=9CI am going t=
o make a fortune making movies and theme parks,=E2=80=9D he says, =E2=80=9C=
and I am giving you the opportunity to invest early. I=E2=80=99m not sellin=
g you shares of my company, though; I=E2=80=99m selling something even bett=
er. Here=E2=80=99s a drawing of a mouse. If you give me $1 million, I will =
use it to build a movie studio and theme-park empire, and the mouse will fe=
ature prominently in that empire, and you will get the royalties from that =
mouse. Here=E2=80=99s a dog, and a duck, and some nephew ducks. Same deal, =
though the nephew=C2=A0ducks are cheaper.=E2=80=9D
Obviously that would, in hindsight, have been a good investment. What kind =
of investment would it have been? Would it have been like=C2=A0buying art?=
=C2=A0Would it have been like=C2=A0buying intellectual property?=C2=A0Or wo=
uld it have been like=C2=A0investing in a speculative business?=C2=A0The mo=
use is a picture of a mouse, like art, but he=E2=80=99s valuable if Disney =
builds a film and theme-park empire and not if he doesn=E2=80=99t, like sto=
ck.
You could expand it. =E2=80=9CI have drawn 101 dalmations,=E2=80=9D he migh=
t go on. =E2=80=9CThey all look like, you know, dalmations. You can buy any=
 one of them, and get the royalties from that dalmation, and use that dalma=
tion in any spinoff intellectual property you want. Dalmation 43 has diamon=
ds on her collar; Dalmation 81=E2=80=99s ears are in sort of a sassy pose; =
maybe those dalmations are worth more, I dunno, what=E2=80=99ll you pay me =
for them?=E2=80=9D
Here=E2=80=99s an SEC=C2=A0NFT enforcement action:

The Securities and Exchange Commission today charged Impact Theory, LLC, a =
media and entertainment company headquartered in Los Angeles, with conducti=
ng an unregistered offering of crypto asset securities in the form of purpo=
rted non-fungible tokens (NFTs). Impact Theory raised approximately $30 mil=
lion from hundreds of investors, including investors across the United Stat=
es, through the offering.
According to the SEC=E2=80=99s order, from October to December 2021, Impact=
 Theory offered and sold three tiers of NFTs, known as Founder=E2=80=99s Ke=
ys, which Impact Theory called =E2=80=9CLegendary,=E2=80=9D =E2=80=9CHeroic=
,=E2=80=9D and =E2=80=9CRelentless.=E2=80=9D The order finds that Impact Th=
eory encouraged potential investors to view the purchase of a Founder=E2=80=
=99s Key as an investment into the business, stating that investors would p=
rofit from their purchases if Impact Theory was successful in its efforts. =
Among other things, Impact Theory emphasized that it was =E2=80=9Ctrying to=
 build the next Disney,=E2=80=9D and, if successful, it would deliver =E2=
=80=9Ctremendous value=E2=80=9D to Founder=E2=80=99s Key purchasers. The or=
der finds that the NFTs offered and sold to investors were investment contr=
acts and therefore securities. Accordingly, Impact Theory violated the fede=
ral securities laws by offering and selling these crypto asset securities t=
o the public in an unregistered offering that was not otherwise exempt from=
 registration.

Impact Theory settled, paying about $6.1 million without admitting or denyi=
ng the charges. I don=E2=80=99t know! On the one hand, in the hypothetical =
Disney case, I think it is not at all clear that the mouse or even the dalm=
ations are securities; they do get their value from Disney=E2=80=99s effort=
s to build a company, but they are independent pieces of intellectual prope=
rty and it seems weird to think of them as securities.
On the other hand, this company wasn=E2=80=99t Disney. The=C2=A0 SEC=E2=80=
=99s order=C2=A0includes some pictures of the NFTs and they are =E2=80=A6=
=C2=A0I dunno, vaguely sci-fi stuff, I=E2=80=99m not even sure what they ar=
e supposed to look like? A plucky young mouse they are not. And:

Impact Theory also underscored that this purported value would be derived f=
rom the company=E2=80=99s efforts, and that Impact Theory would use the pro=
ceeds from the Offering for =E2=80=9Cdevelopment,=E2=80=9D =E2=80=9Cbringin=
g on more team,=E2=80=9D and =E2=80=9Ccreating more projects.=E2=80=9D For =
example, Impact Theory stated:
A. =E2=80=9CBut yeah, I will make sure that we do something that by any rea=
sonable standard, people got a crushing, hilarious amount of value.=E2=80=
=9D
B. =E2=80=9CThe key takeaway that I want you to have is that there is a lot=
 of cool things coming in the next 18 to 24 months. And that is ultimately =
a tiny fraction of the things that will be coming in the next five years. T=
he reason that we=E2=80=99re only selling on the next 18-to-24 month hype i=
s I want you guys to be able to capture 90 percent of the economic value of=
 all the big things that we will do in the coming years beyond that. And th=
e only way to do that is to only sell and set the price based on the things=
 that we=E2=80=99re doing in the short term, and that will leave the upside=
 to be largely captured by you guys.=E2=80=9D
C. =E2=80=9CWe=E2=80=99re going to be investing that money into development=
, into bringing on more team, creating more projects, making sure that we=
=E2=80=99re delivering just an obscene amount of value. Until people are gi=
ggling thinking that they can=E2=80=99t believe that they paid =E2=80=93 yo=
u know =E2=80=93 whichever tier they come in on and are getting all this va=
lue =E2=80=93 until that=E2=80=99s the sentiment =E2=80=93 we will just kee=
p stocking it with value.=E2=80=9D

Yeah sounds like securities. No one is touting the aesthetic value of the N=
FTs,=C2=A0or even=C2=A0saying what the intellectual property franchise woul=
d be; they=E2=80=99re just talking about getting rich.=C2=A0

