style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  explain</a> crypto initial coin of=
ferings by saying that =E2=80=9Cthey=E2=80=99re like if the Wright Brothers=
 sold air miles to finance inventing the airplane,=E2=80=9D so here=E2=80=
=99s another old-timey analogy for non-fungible token offerings. Imagine th=
at one day in the boom times of the 1920s a young animator named Walter Dis=
ney shows up at the stock market one day looking to raise money for his new=
 company. =E2=80=9CI am going to make a fortune making movies and theme par=
ks,=E2=80=9D he says, =E2=80=9Cand I am giving you the opportunity to inves=
t early. I=E2=80=99m not selling you shares of my company, though; I=E2=80=
=99m selling something even better. Here=E2=80=99s a drawing of a mouse. If=
 you give me $1 million, I will use it to build a movie studio and theme-pa=
rk empire, and the mouse will feature prominently in that empire, and you w=
ill get the royalties from that mouse. Here=E2=80=99s a dog, and a duck, an=
d some nephew ducks. Same deal, though the nephew=C2=A0ducks are cheaper.=
=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Obviously that would, in hindsight, have been =
a good investment. What kind of investment would it have been? Would it hav=
e been like=C2=A0<em>buying art?=C2=A0</em>Would it have been like=C2=A0<em=
>buying intellectual property?=C2=A0</em>Or would it have been like=C2=A0<e=
m>investing in a speculative business?=C2=A0</em>The mouse is a picture of =
a mouse, like art, but he=E2=80=99s valuable if Disney builds a film and th=
eme-park empire and not if he doesn=E2=80=99t, like stock.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">You could expand it. =E2=80=9CI have drawn 101=
 dalmations,=E2=80=9D he might go on. =E2=80=9CThey all look like, you know=
, dalmations. You can buy any one of them, and get the royalties from that =
dalmation, and use that dalmation in any spinoff intellectual property you =
want. Dalmation 43 has diamonds on her collar; Dalmation 81=E2=80=99s ears =
are in sort of a sassy pose; maybe those dalmations are worth more, I dunno=
, what=E2=80=99ll you pay me for them?=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Here=E2=80=99s an SEC=C2=A0<a href=3D"https://=
link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/32533691.258429/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjL=
mdvdi9uZXdzL3ByZXNzLXJlbGVhc2UvMjAyMy0xNjM/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB61b8ef9=
3" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=
=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: =
1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-c=
olor: #ccc;">NFT enforcement action</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The Securities and Exchange Commission today c=
harged Impact Theory, LLC, a media and entertainment company headquartered =
in Los Angeles, with conducting an unregistered offering of crypto asset se=
curities in the form of purported non-fungible tokens (NFTs). Impact Theory=
 raised approximately $30 million from hundreds of investors, including inv=
estors across the United States, through the offering.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">According to the SEC=E2=80=99s order, from Oct=
ober to December 2021, Impact Theory offered and sold three tiers of NFTs, =
known as Founder=E2=80=99s Keys, which Impact Theory called =E2=80=9CLegend=
ary,=E2=80=9D =E2=80=9CHeroic,=E2=80=9D and =E2=80=9CRelentless.=E2=80=9D T=
he order finds that Impact Theory encouraged potential investors to view th=
e purchase of a Founder=E2=80=99s Key as an investment into the business, s=
tating that investors would profit from their purchases if Impact Theory wa=
s successful in its efforts. Among other things, Impact Theory emphasized t=
hat it was =E2=80=9Ctrying to build the next Disney,=E2=80=9D and, if succe=
ssful, it would deliver =E2=80=9Ctremendous value=E2=80=9D to Founder=E2=80=
=99s Key purchasers. The order finds that the NFTs offered and sold to inve=
stors were investment contracts and therefore securities. Accordingly, Impa=
ct Theory violated the federal securities laws by offering and selling thes=
e crypto asset securities to the public in an unregistered offering that wa=
s not otherwise exempt from registration.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Impact Theory settled, paying about $6.1 milli=
on without admitting or denying the charges. I don=E2=80=99t know! On the o=
ne hand, in the hypothetical Disney case, I think it is not at all clear th=
at the mouse or even the dalmations are securities; they do get their value=
 from Disney=E2=80=99s efforts to build a company, but they are independent=
 pieces of intellectual property and it seems weird to think of them as sec=
urities.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">On the other hand, this company wasn=E2=80=99t=
 Disney. The=C2=A0<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/=
32533691.258429/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9maWxlcy9saXRpZ2F0aW9uL2FkbWluLzI=
wMjMvMzMtMTEyMjYucGRm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB73f40791" itemprop=3D"StoryL=
ink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; tex=
t-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-colo=
r: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> SEC=E2=80=
=99s order</a>=C2=A0includes some pictures of the NFTs and they are =E2=80=
=A6=C2=A0I dunno, vaguely sci-fi stuff, I=E2=80=99m not even sure what they=
 are supposed to look like? A plucky young mouse they are not. And:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Impact Theory also underscored that this purpo=
rted value would be derived from the company=E2=80=99s efforts, and that Im=
pact Theory would use the proceeds from the Offering for =E2=80=9Cdevelopme=
nt,=E2=80=9D =E2=80=9Cbringing on more team,=E2=80=9D and =E2=80=9Ccreating=
 more projects.=E2=80=9D For example, Impact Theory stated:</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A. =E2=80=9CBut yeah, I will make sure that we=
 do something that by any reasonable standard, people got a crushing, hilar=
ious amount of value.=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">B. =E2=80=9CThe key takeaway that I want you t=
o have is that there is a lot of cool things coming in the next 18 to 24 mo=
nths. And that is ultimately a tiny fraction of the things that will be com=
ing in the next five years. The reason that we=E2=80=99re only selling on t=
he next 18-to-24 month hype is I want you guys to be able to capture 90 per=
cent of the economic value of all the big things that we will do in the com=
ing years beyond that. And the only way to do that is to only sell and set =
the price based on the things that we=E2=80=99re doing in the short term, a=
nd that will leave the upside to be largely captured by you guys.=E2=80=9D<=
/p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">C. =E2=80=9CWe=E2=80=99re going to be investin=
g that money into development, into bringing on more team, creating more pr=
ojects, making sure that we=E2=80=99re delivering just an obscene amount of=
 value. Until people are giggling thinking that they can=E2=80=99t believe =
that they paid =E2=80=93 you know =E2=80=93 whichever tier they come in on =
and are getting all this value =E2=80=93 until that=E2=80=99s the sentiment=
 =E2=80=93 we will just keep stocking it with value.=E2=80=9D</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Yeah sounds like securities. No one is touting=
 the aesthetic value of the NFTs,=C2=A0or even=C2=A0saying what the intelle=
ctual property franchise would be; they=E2=80=99re just talking about getti=
ng rich.=C2=A0</p>
<table class=3D"header" width=3D"100%" border=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" cellp=
