<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A few weeks ago, walking down the street in Mi=
dtown, I saw someone wearing a t-shirt that said =E2=80=9CSilicon Valley Ba=
nk Risk Management Department, Spring 2023.=E2=80=9D I am pretty sure it wa=
s printed as an after-the-fact joke,<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#fo=
otnote-3" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border=
-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none=
 !important; background-color: transparent !important; display: inline-bloc=
k;">
<span>[3]</span>
</a> just because, if Silicon Valley Bank=E2=80=99s risk management departm=
ent had actually had team t-shirts printed in spring 2023, and you got one,=
 you would not go around wearing it, not because you were embarrassed (thou=
gh, maybe?) but=C2=A0because it would be=C2=A0<em>worth $10,000 on eBay</em=
>. Few things are more coveted=C2=A0than the relics of failed financial fir=
ms. I have an FTX water bottle.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And so if you bought Silicon Valley Bank=E2=80=
=99s actual wine collection at a Federal Deposit Insurance Corp. auction, a=
nd you plan to resell it, should you prominently advertise it as being SVB=
=E2=80=99s wine collection? Absolutely! That wine is far more delicious kno=
wing that it came from a failed bank. <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomber=
gbusiness.com/click/32533691.258429/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cud3NqLmNvbS9maW5hbmNlL2J=
hbmtpbmcvd2hvLXdpbnMtd2hlbi1hLWJhbmstZmFpbHMtd2luZS1ndXktZnJhbmstbWFydGVsbC=
00MWQ0NDZjMw/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB826a519b" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" item=
scope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decorat=
ion: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #00000=
0; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> The Wall Street Jo=
urnal reports</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">When [Heritage Auctions wine director Frank]=
=C2=A0Martell heard through the grapevine that the Federal Deposit Insuranc=
e Corp. was having the wine auctioned off, he was eager to jump in. After a=
ll, a rare-coin company buying wine from two collapsed banks seemed, if not=
hing else, weirdly poetic. ...</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">After a number of rounds, Martell won the auct=
ion for the SVB wine lot for roughly $150,000 with fees, a discount of abou=
t 40%. Later, he nabbed the more-than-400-bottle First Republic wine collec=
tion for less than $20,000, at about the same discount. Together the collec=
tions include bottles with price tags that range from $3 to $1,000 a pop.</=
p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Martell estimates that Heritage will make tens=
 of thousands of dollars from the two bank wine collections, some of which =
the company plans to sell at its Fine &amp; Rare Wine Signature Auction in =
Beverly Hills this September. Heritage went back and forth over whether to =
advertise where the wine had come from. It ultimately decided it would.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Correct. SVB was big in the wine lending busin=
ess, but it doesn=E2=80=99t seem like this wine was seized collateral from =
loans gone bad; this was just the corporate collection, I think, kept in =
=E2=80=9Celaborate climate-controlled cellars built within the bank=E2=80=
=99s Santa Clara and Menlo Park branches.=E2=80=9D (Even the $3 bottles?) A=
nyway the FDIC has fun:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">When banks fail, the government can suddenly f=
ind itself in charge of =E2=80=9Cspecialty assets=E2=80=9D that are extrava=
gant, strange=E2=80=94or even in flames.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The oddball asset sales are lore within the FD=
IC. A column in its internal newsletter periodically plumbed the history un=
til the author, Jay Rosenstein, retired in 2020, an agency spokesman said. =
Among the items it recounted: 25,000 pounds of frozen rabbit, a 12% share i=
n the Dallas Cowboys in the late 1980s, a coal mine =E2=80=9Cthat was on fi=
re the day the bank was closed=E2=80=9D and abandoned churches and synagogu=
es. Once, the FDIC seized a Styrofoam cooler that turned out to be holding =
a human skull.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Do you think the FDIC put out the fire? I feel=
 like these days you could make more money by selling =E2=80=9CFailed Bank=
=E2=80=99s Coal Mine, Currently On Fire=E2=80=9D than if you put the fire o=
ut. People want a good disaster story!</p>
